== Japanese ==
[[Image:Japanese Katakana O.png|thumb|right|Katakana character オ]]
===Etymology===
Simplified in the [[w:Heian period|Heian period]] from the ''[[man'yōgana]]'' ([[万葉仮名]]) kanji [[於]] (''o''), taken from the left part of the character.

===Stroke order===
[[Image:Japanese Katakana O Stroke.png]]

===Katakana character===
'''オ''' (''o'')

# the [o] phoneme, typically in words of non-Japanese origins
#: The fifth character of the first column of the [[katakana]] [[syllabary]], it is analogous to [[お]] (''o'') in the [[hiragana]] syllabary. The previous katakana character is [[エ]] (''e'') and the next is [[カ]] (''ka'').

